    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-08-27T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-08-27T01:00:00-05:00" n="1102"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1102">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.801/8–2749: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McConaughy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-27T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 27, 1949—2 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 27—4:20 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3498. A. P. Pattison, local agents Isbrandtsen Co., informed ConGen they plan
                    bring SS <hi rend="italic">Flying Independent</hi> into Shanghai about September
                    9. Vessel will be en route Hong Kong to Taku Bar and is expected load cargo Hong
                    Kong for Shanghai, Shanghai for Tientsin and Shanghai for USA via Suez. Pattison
                    states owners have agreed to call. In view Chinese naval vessel having prevented
                    British SS <hi rend="italic">Edith Moller</hi> from entering Shanghai August 23
                    (refContel 3482, August 26<note n="65" xml:id="d1102fn65">Not printed.</note>),
                    it seems possible <hi rend="italic">Independent</hi> may also be detained.</p>
                <p>Sent Department, repeated Nanking 1849, Hong Kong 212.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McConaughy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
